{"type":"message","id":"3be870bc","parentId":"d930e01d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:20:28.922Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Configuring MCP Settings**\n\nI need to set up the MCP, and I'm thinking I might need to know the configuration format. I'll use the openclaw MCP set for this. For the filesystem, it seems I should be using arguments for the workspace. It could be helpful to inspect the README for the Ollama MCP environment or check the package description for more guidance. I'll gather all the necessary information to make sure I get it right!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_089f5c82f7390fab0169fd1029b64081919bd5857b68aa7a0b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_RAt_GfeadoLX6qxXFjTXM5Jv8Y8AmgG7-fhZk70mDsmnnlVQ_bfsv83Z-FXpQ0Jt8WcAX9Xd-Ed38Hk4owr6nnsHDFDBX6jbh-Gtzk4uHEDQntbd65e3xS3sNqg7kFR-mF2aSqNueAvT9f5KQWwSbVn57OeWgWDU9dxowHvqFmmu4NOiwuUepuMAgxk9Kq-RYGbxuJZEIZuZHuE50cZWehAY8T_62Yj7SU8bElAQkyzVTOfg-J_uqir9dO7E6wSDUb7IWgNDwkrVovpFT3CaI_jfvpGSmnBoGN-q-nBZCBANRTqVRvuBlQPWZcSazWdWbtOxaBEBLGSeNHglZ3I-TqsAUvcasNWyV1XxvRFxEoXXl93LV3cppbNKMG9YK2eBBweDxzZPT01hEDyWOluHHkvxAEYoyfc_nJKkGfC8VDKMjtgVsFsQBwS9CYGvMKVZ6mcF38w3fsBpDD1sm_naSHblO_qyjGpR_kF4kaFA2LYwmCKCE6rHWg_cQ97t0NVK9Hq_Ksy5G7dzGEBq-7BxYJNWMuGjao_IY7LcXHSj0NsW0-qrcBNUWg2bxUkqv4qRcTKMeG_lFWhVMXA4L3onGuYfCLib2KlsZiAyzy8aO-cgpfUXTBtV-mWzrnLjLLKCJqd28M0WmDErJ3SIIGQ1-1wnoCO6Fy7zNjxvjxzS0Zx_2eY8CNs-GbWwYOpjDzmHFfTETOcwx9DNWpo3kjjcuPwUFopGamRfPXZ68dQCSSVDuRoLyysy8gTjBGZY7nHU9vxtPjKbum86Pb2-ViYjpxf5RjYhvqZ5grCarIBgv23Mlb5KBJMe83UFhGDXdAneabS5jdPnOkNUykAknylxQ7v1s74vX9CGwWBcDydqI5fTJS3EbtZQC7WmiJMBoZdHJmcmyrlju419mn88S50eG7ms4JgG_bZl6El8glkYP_1n5siAQ_fvVQVe1nw0vuY8Yp--sr-rC32ngn_sLYznVq25_BvPwx5UvpfkA7ayWxErvA989c52jW0mwpI_mPUIh4Xt_wKHn_rQhHowrmz0Qpu88-YcR3QdifOMgwLJ4BFZO6qLnJtsvbuDnQPO7iZBIi3IT4ibXyLf5ZDODyS6pCZnSf2-Tck6fWNpB4fu3vteZo=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Configuring MCP Settings**\\n\\nI need to set up the MCP, and I'm thinking I might need to know the configuration format. I'll use the openclaw MCP set for this. For the filesystem, it seems I should be using arguments for the workspace. It could be helpful to inspect the README for the Ollama MCP environment or check the package description for more guidance. I'll gather all the necessary information to make sure I get it right!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"🧑🏼‍💻 [เรียกใช้เครื่องมือ: exec]","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_089f5c82f7390fab0169fd102dd46881918a265f2e349fd4d7\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_usZCPMshH9YDTn3AFJ6Xdslc|fc_089f5c82f7390fab0169fd102de1ec8191a493ad744bd37991","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"set -e\ncd ~/.openclaw/mcp-node\nprintf '%s\\n' '--- ollama readme head ---'\nsed -n '1,180p' node_modules/ollama-mcp-server/README.md 2>/dev/null || true\nprintf '%s\\n' '--- filesystem readme usage ---'\ngrep -n \"Usage\\|command\\|args\\|npx\\|filesystem\" node_modules/@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem/README.md | sed -n '1,80p' || true","workdir":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":647,"output":220,"cacheRead":37888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38755,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778192423718,"responseId":"resp_089f5c82f7390fab0169fd1029056c8191afb63ddbc89ddc12"}}
{"type":"message","id":"05262dc9","parentId":"3be870bc","timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:20:28.944Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_usZCPMshH9YDTn3AFJ6Xdslc|fc_089f5c82f7390fab0169fd102de1ec8191a493ad744bd37991","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"--- ollama readme head ---\n# Ollama MCP Server\n\n> **This is a rebooted and actively maintained fork.**  \n> Original project: [NightTrek/Ollama-mcp](https://github.com/NightTrek/Ollama-mcp)  \n>  \n> This repository ([hyzhak/ollama-mcp-server](https://github.com/hyzhak/ollama-mcp-server)) is a fresh upstream with improved maintenance, metadata, and publishing automation.  \n>  \n> See [NightTrek/Ollama-mcp](https://github.com/NightTrek/Ollama-mcp) for project history and prior releases.\n\n🚀 A powerful bridge between Ollama and the Model Context Protocol (MCP), enabling seamless integration of Ollama's local LLM capabilities into your MCP-powered applications.\n\n## 🌟 Features\n\n### Complete Ollama Integration\n- **Full API Coverage**: Access all essential Ollama functionality through a clean MCP interface\n- **OpenAI-Compatible Chat**: Drop-in replacement for OpenAI's chat completion API\n- **Local LLM Power**: Run AI models locally with full control and privacy\n\n### Core Capabilities\n- 🔄 **Model Management**\n  - Pull models from registries\n  - Push models to registries\n  - List available models\n  - Create custom models from Modelfiles\n  - Copy and remove models\n\n- 🤖 **Model Execution**\n  - Run models with customizable prompts (response is returned only after completion; streaming is not supported in stdio mode)\n  - Vision/multimodal support: pass images to compatible models\n  - Chat completion API with system/user/assistant roles\n  - Configurable parameters (temperature, timeout)\n  - **NEW:** `think` parameter for advanced reasoning and transparency (see below)\n  - Raw mode support for direct responses\n\n- 🛠 **Server Control**\n  - Start and manage Ollama server\n  - View detailed model information\n  - Error handling and timeout management\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- [Ollama](https://ollama.ai) installed on your system\n- Node.js (with [npx](https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/commands/npx), included with npm)\n\n\n### Configuration\n\nAdd the server to your MCP configuration:\n\n#### For Claude Desktop:\nMacOS: `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`\nWindows: `%APPDATA%/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"ollama\": {\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"ollama-mcp-server\"],\n      \"env\": {\n        \"OLLAMA_HOST\": \"http://127.0.0.1:11434\"  // Optional: customize Ollama API endpoint\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🛠 Developer Setup\n\n### Prerequisites\n- [Ollama](https://ollama.ai) installed on your system\n- Node.js and npm\n\n### Installation\n\n1. Install dependencies:\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\n2. Build the server:\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n## 🛠 Usage Examples\n\n### Pull and Run a Model\n```typescript\n// Pull a model\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"pull\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"llama2\"\n  }\n});\n\n// Run the model\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"run\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"llama2\",\n    prompt: \"Explain quantum computing in simple terms\"\n  }\n});\n```\n\n### Run a Vision/Multimodal Model\n\n```typescript\n// Run a model with an image (for vision/multimodal models)\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"run\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"gemma3:4b\",\n    prompt: \"Describe the contents of this image.\",\n    imagePath: \"./path/to/image.jpg\"\n  }\n});\n```\n\n### Chat Completion (OpenAI-compatible)\n```typescript\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"chat_completion\",\n  arguments: {\n    model: \"llama2\",\n    messages: [\n      {\n        role: \"system\",\n        content: \"You are a helpful assistant.\"\n      },\n      {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"What is the meaning of life?\"\n      }\n    ],\n    temperature: 0.7\n  }\n});\n\n// Chat with images (for vision/multimodal models)\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"chat_completion\",\n  arguments: {\n    model: \"gemma3:4b\",\n    messages: [\n      {\n        role: \"system\",\n        content: \"You are a helpful assistant.\"\n      },\n      {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"Describe the contents of this image.\",\n        images: [\"./path/to/image.jpg\"]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n});\n```\n> Note: The `images` field is optional and only supported by vision/multimodal models.\n\n### Create Custom Model\n```typescript\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"create\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"custom-model\",\n    modelfile: \"./path/to/Modelfile\"\n  }\n--- filesystem readme usage ---\n3:Node.js server implementing Model Context Protocol (MCP) for filesystem operations.\n16:The server uses a flexible directory access control system. Directories can be specified via command-line arguments or dynamically via [Roots](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/learn/client-concepts#roots).\n21:mcp-server-filesystem /path/to/dir1 /path/to/dir2\n29:**Important**: If server starts without command-line arguments AND client doesn't support roots protocol (or provides empty roots), the server will throw an error during initialization.\n38:   - Server starts with directories from command-line arguments (if provided)\n53:   - Server continues using command-line directories only\n57:   - All filesystem operations are restricted to allowed directories\n61:**Note**: The server will only allow operations within directories specified either via `args` or via Roots.\n187:The mapping for filesystem tools is:\n207:## Usage with Claude Desktop\n218:    \"filesystem\": {\n219:      \"command\": \"docker\",\n220:      \"args\": [\n227:        \"mcp/filesystem\",\n240:    \"filesystem\": {\n241:      \"command\": \"npx\",\n242:      \"args\": [\n244:        \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem\",\n253:## Usage with VS Code\n257:[![Install with NPX in VS Code](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code-NPM-0098FF?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22npx%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22-y%22%2C%22%40modelcontextprotocol%2Fserver-filesystem%22%2C%22%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%22%5D%7D) [![Install with NPX in VS Code Insiders](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code_Insiders-NPM-24bfa5?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22npx%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22-y%22%2C%22%40modelcontextprotocol%2Fserver-filesystem%22%2C%22%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%22%5D%7D&quality=insiders)\n259:[![Install with Docker in VS Code](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code-Docker-0098FF?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22docker%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22run%22%2C%22-i%22%2C%22--rm%22%2C%22--mount%22%2C%22type%3Dbind%2Csrc%3D%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%2Cdst%3D%2Fprojects%2Fworkspace%22%2C%22mcp%2Ffilesystem%22%2C%22%2Fprojects%22%5D%7D) [![Install with Docker in VS Code Insiders](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code_Insiders-Docker-24bfa5?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22docker%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22run%22%2C%22-i%22%2C%22--rm%22%2C%22--mount%22%2C%22type%3Dbind%2Csrc%3D%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%2Cdst%3D%2Fprojects%2Fworkspace%22%2C%22mcp%2Ffilesystem%22%2C%22%2Fprojects%22%5D%7D&quality=insiders)\n279:    \"filesystem\": {\n280:      \"command\": \"docker\",\n281:      \"args\": [\n286:        \"mcp/filesystem\",\n299:    \"filesystem\": {\n300:      \"command\": \"npx\",\n301:      \"args\": [\n303:        \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem\",\n316:docker build -t mcp/filesystem -f src/filesystem/Dockerfile ."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"--- ollama readme head ---\n# Ollama MCP Server\n\n> **This is a rebooted and actively maintained fork.**  \n> Original project: [NightTrek/Ollama-mcp](https://github.com/NightTrek/Ollama-mcp)  \n>  \n> This repository ([hyzhak/ollama-mcp-server](https://github.com/hyzhak/ollama-mcp-server)) is a fresh upstream with improved maintenance, metadata, and publishing automation.  \n>  \n> See [NightTrek/Ollama-mcp](https://github.com/NightTrek/Ollama-mcp) for project history and prior releases.\n\n🚀 A powerful bridge between Ollama and the Model Context Protocol (MCP), enabling seamless integration of Ollama's local LLM capabilities into your MCP-powered applications.\n\n## 🌟 Features\n\n### Complete Ollama Integration\n- **Full API Coverage**: Access all essential Ollama functionality through a clean MCP interface\n- **OpenAI-Compatible Chat**: Drop-in replacement for OpenAI's chat completion API\n- **Local LLM Power**: Run AI models locally with full control and privacy\n\n### Core Capabilities\n- 🔄 **Model Management**\n  - Pull models from registries\n  - Push models to registries\n  - List available models\n  - Create custom models from Modelfiles\n  - Copy and remove models\n\n- 🤖 **Model Execution**\n  - Run models with customizable prompts (response is returned only after completion; streaming is not supported in stdio mode)\n  - Vision/multimodal support: pass images to compatible models\n  - Chat completion API with system/user/assistant roles\n  - Configurable parameters (temperature, timeout)\n  - **NEW:** `think` parameter for advanced reasoning and transparency (see below)\n  - Raw mode support for direct responses\n\n- 🛠 **Server Control**\n  - Start and manage Ollama server\n  - View detailed model information\n  - Error handling and timeout management\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- [Ollama](https://ollama.ai) installed on your system\n- Node.js (with [npx](https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/commands/npx), included with npm)\n\n\n### Configuration\n\nAdd the server to your MCP configuration:\n\n#### For Claude Desktop:\nMacOS: `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`\nWindows: `%APPDATA%/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"ollama\": {\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"ollama-mcp-server\"],\n      \"env\": {\n        \"OLLAMA_HOST\": \"http://127.0.0.1:11434\"  // Optional: customize Ollama API endpoint\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🛠 Developer Setup\n\n### Prerequisites\n- [Ollama](https://ollama.ai) installed on your system\n- Node.js and npm\n\n### Installation\n\n1. Install dependencies:\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\n2. Build the server:\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n## 🛠 Usage Examples\n\n### Pull and Run a Model\n```typescript\n// Pull a model\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"pull\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"llama2\"\n  }\n});\n\n// Run the model\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"run\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"llama2\",\n    prompt: \"Explain quantum computing in simple terms\"\n  }\n});\n```\n\n### Run a Vision/Multimodal Model\n\n```typescript\n// Run a model with an image (for vision/multimodal models)\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"run\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"gemma3:4b\",\n    prompt: \"Describe the contents of this image.\",\n    imagePath: \"./path/to/image.jpg\"\n  }\n});\n```\n\n### Chat Completion (OpenAI-compatible)\n```typescript\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"chat_completion\",\n  arguments: {\n    model: \"llama2\",\n    messages: [\n      {\n        role: \"system\",\n        content: \"You are a helpful assistant.\"\n      },\n      {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"What is the meaning of life?\"\n      }\n    ],\n    temperature: 0.7\n  }\n});\n\n// Chat with images (for vision/multimodal models)\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"chat_completion\",\n  arguments: {\n    model: \"gemma3:4b\",\n    messages: [\n      {\n        role: \"system\",\n        content: \"You are a helpful assistant.\"\n      },\n      {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: \"Describe the contents of this image.\",\n        images: [\"./path/to/image.jpg\"]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n});\n```\n> Note: The `images` field is optional and only supported by vision/multimodal models.\n\n### Create Custom Model\n```typescript\nawait mcp.use_mcp_tool({\n  server_name: \"ollama\",\n  tool_name: \"create\",\n  arguments: {\n    name: \"custom-model\",\n    modelfile: \"./path/to/Modelfile\"\n  }\n--- filesystem readme usage ---\n3:Node.js server implementing Model Context Protocol (MCP) for filesystem operations.\n16:The server uses a flexible directory access control system. Directories can be specified via command-line arguments or dynamically via [Roots](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/learn/client-concepts#roots).\n21:mcp-server-filesystem /path/to/dir1 /path/to/dir2\n29:**Important**: If server starts without command-line arguments AND client doesn't support roots protocol (or provides empty roots), the server will throw an error during initialization.\n38:   - Server starts with directories from command-line arguments (if provided)\n53:   - Server continues using command-line directories only\n57:   - All filesystem operations are restricted to allowed directories\n61:**Note**: The server will only allow operations within directories specified either via `args` or via Roots.\n187:The mapping for filesystem tools is:\n207:## Usage with Claude Desktop\n218:    \"filesystem\": {\n219:      \"command\": \"docker\",\n220:      \"args\": [\n227:        \"mcp/filesystem\",\n240:    \"filesystem\": {\n241:      \"command\": \"npx\",\n242:      \"args\": [\n244:        \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem\",\n253:## Usage with VS Code\n257:[![Install with NPX in VS Code](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code-NPM-0098FF?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22npx%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22-y%22%2C%22%40modelcontextprotocol%2Fserver-filesystem%22%2C%22%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%22%5D%7D) [![Install with NPX in VS Code Insiders](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code_Insiders-NPM-24bfa5?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22npx%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22-y%22%2C%22%40modelcontextprotocol%2Fserver-filesystem%22%2C%22%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%22%5D%7D&quality=insiders)\n259:[![Install with Docker in VS Code](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code-Docker-0098FF?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22docker%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22run%22%2C%22-i%22%2C%22--rm%22%2C%22--mount%22%2C%22type%3Dbind%2Csrc%3D%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%2Cdst%3D%2Fprojects%2Fworkspace%22%2C%22mcp%2Ffilesystem%22%2C%22%2Fprojects%22%5D%7D) [![Install with Docker in VS Code Insiders](https://img.shields.io/badge/VS_Code_Insiders-Docker-24bfa5?style=flat-square&logo=visualstudiocode&logoColor=white)](https://insiders.vscode.dev/redirect/mcp/install?name=filesystem&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22docker%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22run%22%2C%22-i%22%2C%22--rm%22%2C%22--mount%22%2C%22type%3Dbind%2Csrc%3D%24%7BworkspaceFolder%7D%2Cdst%3D%2Fprojects%2Fworkspace%22%2C%22mcp%2Ffilesystem%22%2C%22%2Fprojects%22%5D