{"type":"message","id":"5ee53749","parentId":"97065022","timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:48:31.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering tool log adjustments**\n\nThe user seems to suggest they want to declutter unwanted tool log messages. They mentioned our Identify Yourself instruction, so maybe I should agree and stop announcing tool logs, except for Facefy. However, they didn't explicitly ask for this, but context hints at wanting auto-deletion. We don't have a delete tool, and there’s a conflict because they previously wanted Identify Yourself to be announced. Maybe I need to modify the instruction to avoid logging during normal chats?\n\n**Updating memory and tool usage**\n\nI need to figure out how to align the tool usage with the user’s feedback. They’re expressing concerns about clutter from announcements, yet we still need to respect previous memory instructions. Maybe I can avoid using \"เรียกใช้เครื่องมือ\" for logs and focus on being concise. I’ll ensure to implement the newest requests regarding the MCP sequence while minimizing disruptions, using a Thai prefix and suffix. I’ll also check prior preferences with memory_search and use tools in commentary without extra noise.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_089f5c82f7390fab0169fd16b5a17481919c3ba5baa6a56546\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_RbAWvD8T4-TibcWd2x4X0kucEGRgFkmBk21B4DsggWpMVHOiZ6ChtfemLtGXblpxFPWyaHIKlDULay0dH_tTVE4PRM6Z1r7w3xTDDSnIHLT--9d-Ev1_qneCL9tGXazNZWYmKGzQqOJ9C9doDhC55OjD93gpDkrxHsBAGL7iLUZbF1jfgzi_hF48pxmzYu5J6voTeWy-xffF1DEmI8_ftkttdvmD_d3lwskIkTkajsSKs2zqI8pQ28R3-zFMSOUiPhMBp1Yn91EyXESCQ1GybQ6NAOowyHhGQxj6X9LZRMHjwpvoHu52SAOO4twPpwZgDqXX6O-rHfv4XFpuPGQmQRf1EZLh6U5uaFgt0EkFJJhnsiFWM0M4tSJvyUpcTFKfDo-EJUD2mnZMg-FDSLkfFzTfzvL1v8tizha7t7t8xcP7GG-4n6w5gjtGBM2npNm8qo1CiOBf9vEjT3qtt61ZQURbSaQ1qNW201gws4_fWfCmn-zxcRKQQ-WsvWVrvkIEGxGhqk7Fj9jhELeIsyVeUzFqIQLoiWxm0k5wTfgaw9uovYcu_TSQ5gonedsBAT_CkmiKxveLNhsf1GET8Da1NCMw9C-gky